      "id": "ed2d2b91cf36fbc6",
      "text": "It can be used to power Instant Messaging, VoIP/WebRTC signalling, or [[Internet of Things]] communication"
    },
    {
      "type": "markdown",
      "id": "f0f1154c4053d3ee",
      "text": "# Matrix Widgets"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "id": "97dceb2826d5ddaf",
      "text": "Widgets are a deceptively simple idea: the ability to pin small form-factor webapps (called widgets) into a given Matrix room, letting admins build up a dashboard of functionality which is then in common and automatically available to everyone who views that room.  You can think of it as being similar to installing an app onto a smartphone, but instead pulling it into a Matrix conversation.  "
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "id": "e53c73edae11c03a",
      "text": "This could be a [[Jitsi]] video conference, or a collaborative document editor, or a [[Grafana]] dashboard, or anything you can imagine really (assuming its security headers support embedding) - [https://matrix.org/blog/2017/08/23/introducing-matrix-widgets/ matrix.org]"
    },
