        "id": "d3724e68ea9f05ba",
        "text": "# What does Matrix provide?\n"
      },
      "date": 1458843364149
    },
    {
      "type": "edit",
      "id": "3dbbdb09513b38a0",
      "item": {
        "type": "markdown",
        "id": "3dbbdb09513b38a0",
        "text": "# What is Matrix’s Mission?"
      },
      "date": 1458843368831
    },
    {
      "type": "edit",
      "id": "6ba1432077bc1a95",
      "item": {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "id": "6ba1432077bc1a95",
        "text": "Matrix is an open standard for interoperable, decentralised, real-time communication over IP. It can be used to power Instant Messaging, VoIP/WebRTC signalling, Internet of Things communication - or anywhere you need a standard HTTP API for publishing and subscribing to data whilst tracking the conversation history - [http://matrix.org/docs/guides/faq.html#general matrix.org]"
      },
      "date": 1458843392610
    },
    {
      "type": "edit",
      "id": "25f43c3e57f2996d",
      "item": {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "id": "25f43c3e57f2996d",
        "text": "Matrix’s initial goal is to fix the problem of fragmented IP communications: letting users message and call each other without having to care what app the other user is on - making it as easy as sending an email.\n"
      },
      "date": 1458843420523
    },
    {
      "type": "add",
      "id": "2fc475ab5c2ecfe7",
      "item": {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "id": "2fc475ab5c2ecfe7",
        "text": "The longer term goal is for Matrix to act as a generic HTTP messaging and data synchronisation system for the whole web - allowing people, services and devices to easily communicate with each other, empowering users to own and control their data and select the services and vendors they want to use."
      },
      "after": "25f43c3e57f2996d",
      "date": 1458843423059
    },
    {
      "type": "edit",
      "id": "3f0f1809d631463b",
      "item": {
        "type": "markdown",
        "id": "3f0f1809d631463b",
        "text": "Matrix provides:\n* Open Standard HTTP APIs for transferring JSON messages (e.g. instant messages, WebRTC signalling), including:\n* Client<->Server API - defines how Matrix compatible clients communicate with Matrix homeservers.\n* Server<->Server API - defines how Matrix homeservers exchange messages and synchronise history with each other.\n* Application Service API - defines how to extend the functionality of Matrix with ‘integrations’ and bridge to other networks.\n* Modules - specifies features that must be implemented by particular classes of clients.\n* Open source reference implementations of:\nClients (Web (React), iOS, Android)\nClient SDKs (Javascript, Web (React), iOS, Android)\n* Homeservers (Synapse) - [https://github.com/matrix-org/synapse github]\n* Application Services (bridges to IRC, Slack, Skype, Lync and more…)\n"
      },
      "date": 1458843472886
    },
